body:
2D array assignment doesn't seem to be working when assigned in a module port.

## Steps to reproduce the issue

1. Download and extract [broken.zip](https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys/files/5900089/broken.zip). It contains one file broken.sv.
2. Run `yosys -p "read_verilog -sv broken.sv; synth_ice40; write_verilog"`
3. Observe the value assigned to `out`

I have rebuilt from master, and verified that this behaviour still occurs, my version is:
`Yosys 0.9+3882 (git sha1 beeaad19, clang 11.0.0 -fPIC -Os)`

Here are the contents of broken.sv for reference:
```
module intermediate
(    
    output logic [3:0] out
);
    assign out = 4'hA;
endmodule

module broken
(
    output logic [3:0] out
); 
    // Works - out is assigned 4'hA
    //logic [3:0] vec [0:0];
    //assign vec[0] = 4'hA;
    //assign out = vec[0];

    // Works - out is assigned 4'hA
    //logic [3:0] vec;
    //intermediate inst (.out(vec[3:0]));
    //assign out = vec[3:0];

    // Doesn't work - out is assigned 4'hX
    logic [3:0] vec [0:0];
    intermediate inst (.out(vec[0]));
    assign out = vec[0];
endmodule
```

## Expected behavior
`out` is assigned is assigned 4'hA.

## Actual behavior

`out` is assigned is assigned 4'hX.

